03:07.437 --> 03:09.882
Kleinman! Kleinman, open up.

03:10.482 --> 03:13.276
- Kleinman!
- We know you're in there.

03:13.860 --> 03:15.487
- Kleinman!
- You bastard!

03:16.113 --> 03:18.457
Open the door. Kleinman!

03:18.949 --> 03:20.225
Come on, Kleinman.

03:20.325 --> 03:21.952
Kleinman!

03:22.744 --> 03:25.230
I'm coming, I'm coming.

03:25.330 --> 03:27.082
- Kleinman!
- Kleinman, come on.

03:27.290 --> 03:29.192
- What?
- For God's sake, Kleinman, are you deaf?

03:29.292 --> 03:31.862
What do you mean, deaf?
What's, what's... What's going on?

03:31.962 --> 03:33.905
- We need you to get dressed.
- Get dressed? Why?

03:34.005 --> 03:34.990
Don't play ignorant.

03:35.090 --> 03:36.867
I was playing ignorant?
I was in a deep sleep.

03:36.967 --> 03:40.203
- We expect the killer to strike again tonight.
- The killer? What killer?

03:40.303 --> 03:41.413
The strangler.

03:41.513 --> 03:43.165
- What strangler?
- The maniac.

03:43.265 --> 03:45.709
The one who killed Eisler's son
and choked Jensen to death

03:45.809 --> 03:47.085
with the piano wire.

03:47.185 --> 03:48.587
Jenson?

03:48.687 --> 03:51.214
The big night watchman?

03:51.314 --> 03:53.817
That's right. Took him from behind.

03:54.109 --> 03:55.886
Crept up, got him by the throat.

03:55.986 --> 03:57.846
He was blue when we found him.

03:57.946 --> 04:00.790
Saliva frozen down the corner
of his mouth.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.895
Well, look, I've got to be up
early tomorrow for work, so...

04:04.995 --> 04:06.855
Don't play dumb, Kleinman.
You live on an island?

04:06.955 --> 04:09.316
Tonight's a foggy night.
He always strikes in the fog.

04:09.416 --> 04:10.400
Yeah, but, you see, I...

04:10.500 --> 04:12.361
This is a very busy time
for me in my firm.

04:12.461 --> 04:16.490
You know, I'm in competition
for a promotion with Simon Carr...

04:16.589 --> 04:18.742
Don't you know no one can walk
the streets at night?

04:18.841 --> 04:19.910
Yeah, well, you know, I hear certain...

04:20.010 --> 04:21.244
And it's not just the streets.

04:21.344 --> 04:23.372
The Quilty sisters
were killed in their own home

04:23.472 --> 04:24.831
because they didn't lock the door.

04:24.931 --> 04:26.708
Throats cut from ear to ear.

04:26.808 --> 04:27.918
I thought you said he was a strangler.

04:28.018 --> 04:29.378
Does it matter how he kills?

04:29.478 --> 04:30.921
So angry, what is he...

04:31.021 --> 04:33.090
Hey, what's he gettin' so angry for?
Okay.

04:33.190 --> 04:34.863
Okay. There's no motive?

04:35.025 --> 04:36.259
So, you know about it.

04:36.359 --> 04:39.763
Well, you know,
I hear, now and then, a drib and drab.

04:39.863 --> 04:41.431
He hears what he wants to hear.

04:41.531 --> 04:42.516
Get dressed.

04:42.616 --> 04:44.434
What do you mean, get dressed?
This is police business.

04:44.534 --> 04:45.519
The police have had their chance.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.104
Now we're taking matters
into our own hands.

04:47.204 --> 04:48.188
No, that's scary.

04:48.288 --> 04:49.564
You're one of us, aren't you, Kleinman?

04:49.664 --> 04:51.108
Yes, yes, I'm definitely one of you.

04:51.208 --> 04:52.275
What do you want me to do?

04:52.375 --> 04:53.694
We have a plan to trap him.

04:53.794 --> 04:54.861
Yeah, but, what kind of plan?

04:54.961 --> 04:55.987
It's Hacker's. He should tell it.

04:56.087 --> 04:57.072
What, well, Hacker, what's...

04:57.172 --> 04:58.240
You'll find out your assignment.

04:58.340 --> 04:59.950
Get dressed. You're wasting time.

05:00.050 --> 05:02.052
- What do you mean?
- We'll meet you downstairs in five minutes.

05:02.594 --> 05:03.620
Well, okay, but...

05:03.720 --> 05:05.956
My theory is that
it's someone that we all know.

05:06.056 --> 05:08.625
Someone, you know, that we work
next to or go to church with.

05:08.725 --> 05:11.228
He lurks in the shadows,
waiting to pounce.

05:11.561 --> 05:15.156
But, you see,
I was in a deep sleep, so I was...

05:16.733 --> 05:18.802
What is this plan? How can I be of help?

05:18.902 --> 05:21.325
Kleinman. Kleinman. In, in, in, in.

05:23.907 --> 05:25.454
Kleinman, here.

05:26.493 --> 05:28.228
- I brought you some pepper.
- Pepper? What...

05:28.328 --> 05:29.354
I overheard everything.

05:29.454 --> 05:32.315
If you're caught by the maniac,
blow pepper in his eyes.

05:32.415 --> 05:35.652
Yes, very good.
I'll ward him off with a seasoning.

05:35.752 --> 05:38.238
This is ridiculous. I'm petrified.
I'm not gonna go out.

05:38.338 --> 05:39.656
Be a man, Kleinman.

05:39.756 --> 05:40.741
What do you mean, be a man?

05:40.841 --> 05:44.286
Suddenly, in the middle of the night,
I gotta put on a suit and a tie and...

05:44.386 --> 05:45.412
What do you need a tie for?

05:45.512 --> 05:48.061
You're going to hunt
for a homicidal maniac.

05:48.807 --> 05:52.085
Do I know who I'll run into out there?
What if I see my boss?

05:52.185 --> 05:53.628
You know, Mr. Paulsen is funny that way.

05:53.728 --> 05:58.091
And there's a big competition between
me and Simon Carr for this promotion.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.968
What are you
killing yourself for that promotion?

06:00.068 --> 06:02.304
What does it mean? An extra few dollars?

06:02.404 --> 06:04.514
No, I told you. It isn't the money.

06:04.614 --> 06:05.599
I wanna amount to something.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.142
Why should Carr get the promotion?

06:07.242 --> 06:09.352
You know, because
he takes Paulsen to dinner all the time?

06:09.452 --> 06:11.813
I mean, you're
too frightened of Mr. Paulsen.

06:11.913 --> 06:13.523
You cringe in front of him like a worm.

06:13.623 --> 06:16.610
Well, he makes me nervous.
And I don't cringe.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.779
Calling your boss
"Your Majesty" is cringing.

06:18.879 --> 06:22.073
Stop it. I don't like this.
I don't wanna have to go out.

06:22.173 --> 06:24.576
I was in a nice warm bed.
Suddenly I'm part of a plan.

06:24.676 --> 06:26.787
When are you gonna
come to your senses and marry me?

06:26.887 --> 06:28.330
You could tell your boss to stuff it

06:28.430 --> 06:30.248
and you'd own half of this whole place.

06:30.348 --> 06:31.875
I'm not gonna marry you.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.460
I have a fiancée. What are you...

06:33.560 --> 06:35.437
Some fiancée.

06:35.562 --> 06:38.048
Eve wants you for an ornament,
if you get the promotion.

06:38.148 --> 06:39.716
Don't... Don't talk about Eve.

06:39.816 --> 06:42.302
I don't wanna discuss this all the time.
Eve is a lovely creature.

06:42.402 --> 06:45.155
Eve treats you like scum. Be careful.

06:45.322 --> 06:46.890
I'd hate for them to find you
in an alley

06:46.990 --> 06:49.618
with your throat slit from ear to ear.

06:50.201 --> 06:53.125
Don't worry about that.
He mostly strangles.

07:09.262 --> 07:10.855
Gee, it's empty.

07:11.473 --> 07:13.942
Where, where is everybody?

07:14.351 --> 07:16.524
They're supposed to be here.

07:17.312 --> 07:19.314
Where the hell did they go?

07:19.689 --> 07:21.691
The street's so desolate.

07:23.568 --> 07:26.913
I don't like this.
I wanna get back into bed.

07:27.781 --> 07:29.599
I can't do that, though.

07:29.699 --> 07:34.079
If something goes wrong
with their plan, they'll say it's my fault.

07:35.872 --> 07:37.089
Why me?

08:05.610 --> 08:09.911
I'm an artist. Every town we played in,
I'd get huge laughs.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.041
And here, nothing.

08:12.200 --> 08:15.854
I mean, no one comes, and the few that do
just sit there stone-faced.

08:15.954 --> 08:18.440
I know. I was very little
appreciated myself.

08:18.540 --> 08:19.649
None of us were.

08:19.749 --> 08:22.652
Well, your specialty
is quite different to mine.

08:22.752 --> 08:25.155
I don't know about that.
I, I was thinking you can tell a lot

08:25.255 --> 08:28.533
about an audience by how they respond to
a good sword-swallower.

08:28.633 --> 08:30.911
Mmm, believe me,
nothing is more terrifying

08:31.011 --> 08:34.121
than attempting to
make people laugh, and failing.

08:34.222 --> 08:35.874
So, why do we put up with it?

08:35.974 --> 08:40.211
When we pull out tomorrow, why don't
we just tell Danzig we're quitting?

08:40.311 --> 08:41.337
To do what?

08:41.438 --> 08:43.048
Well, settle down.

08:43.148 --> 08:45.050
Where we don't have
to travel all the time,

08:45.150 --> 08:47.653
where it's not such a grueling life.

08:47.902 --> 08:50.847
Get married, you know.
Live like other people.

08:50.947 --> 08:54.577
We're not like other people.
We're artists.

08:55.452 --> 08:57.771
With great talent comes responsibility.

08:57.871 --> 09:01.900
But it would be so nice.
You could find a job someplace.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.861
But then doing what?
Collecting other people's refuse?

09:04.961 --> 09:06.279
- No.
- Sweeping the streets?

09:06.379 --> 09:08.031
Of course not. No, you're clever.

09:08.131 --> 09:10.075
Somebody'd give you an opportunity.

09:10.175 --> 09:13.975
But I have a rare opportunity now,
to make people laugh.

09:14.471 --> 09:16.815
To make them forget their sad lives.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.794
Listen, it's not my fault
that this stupid traveling show

09:20.894 --> 09:23.147
is completely mismanaged.

09:23.897 --> 09:28.949
I'm sure Danzig steals
every cent of profit.

09:29.277 --> 09:30.804
I wanna have a baby.

09:30.904 --> 09:33.598
We're going to have a baby,
but not right now.

09:33.698 --> 09:37.498
A family? That's death to the artist.
I need peace and quiet.

09:38.161 --> 09:41.665
I mean, you know, my mind...
It's funny...

09:42.207 --> 09:44.710
It's just constantly filled with, um,

09:45.376 --> 09:49.656
new routines, ideas, gags,
brilliant and creative twists.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.408
Why don't you tell the truth?

09:51.508 --> 09:53.076
You don't want to get married.

09:53.176 --> 09:56.897
So, you can play cards
and flirt with all the adoring ladies.

09:57.013 --> 09:58.498
- That's not true.
- Oh, yes, it is.

09:58.598 --> 10:02.535
I just want to...
I have to make a name for myself first.

10:02.735 --> 10:04.688
We will get...

10:05.897 --> 10:07.132
You know, I love you.

10:07.232 --> 10:09.075
No. You keep promising.

10:09.692 --> 10:13.162
But soon it's gonna
be too late for me to have a baby.

10:13.571 --> 10:16.324
But, too... Don't cry.

10:17.826 --> 10:19.686
Listen, I'll talk to Danzig.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.021
You don't mean it.

10:21.121 --> 10:24.216
I do mean it. Stop.
You know I can't stand that.

10:24.749 --> 10:26.092
Don't cry.

10:57.323 --> 10:59.746
The audience was too quiet tonight.

11:00.368 --> 11:02.166
I felt sorry for you.

11:02.787 --> 11:05.656
You're the only one they seem to like.

11:06.071 --> 11:08.985
Yeah, but I have
my little tricks for seducing them.

11:09.085 --> 11:10.177
Yes.

11:12.213 --> 11:15.137
What are you doing
wandering around out here?

11:15.633 --> 11:18.136
I was on my way to speak to Danzig.

11:18.261 --> 11:19.262
Mmm.

11:20.054 --> 11:21.772
Like Irish whiskey?

11:22.223 --> 11:26.820
Uh, yes, but my doctor
says it's very bad for my stomach.

11:27.395 --> 11:29.693
Oh. That's too bad.

11:32.775 --> 11:34.118
But, uh...

11:35.737 --> 11:38.490
It's probably relaxing.

11:49.292 --> 11:51.361
The most voluptuous woman in the circus.

11:51.461 --> 11:54.931
It would be my luck
she'd be married to the strongman.

11:55.798 --> 11:59.519
Don't worry about Peter.
He's had a gallon of this already.

12:03.139 --> 12:06.313
You know, sometimes
when you're up on the high wire,

12:06.517 --> 12:08.690
I look at you. You look so...

12:11.439 --> 12:12.841
What?

12:12.941 --> 12:15.114
Mmm. Edible.

12:18.071 --> 12:19.994
How hungry are you now?

12:20.949 --> 12:24.294
I'm always famished after a performance.
And you?

12:25.703 --> 12:28.331
I can never sleep on an empty stomach.

12:29.499 --> 12:32.252
Do you have a taste
for anything special?

12:33.628 --> 12:37.178
I'm not fussy.
I eat what you put in front of me.

12:38.174 --> 12:40.869
And you're sure
your husband won't wake up?

12:40.969 --> 12:43.997
I mean, I have seen
what he does to iron bars.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.020
Nothing wakes Peter up.

12:46.933 --> 12:49.937
Certainly not the sound
of two people moaning.

13:02.407 --> 13:05.536
Oh, you.
I thought I saw you come in here.

13:05.827 --> 13:07.770
- Hey...
- Rat! You rat!

13:07.870 --> 13:08.980
Irmy!

13:09.080 --> 13:10.857
You said you were going to Danzig.

13:10.957 --> 13:12.901
You were supposed to go to Danzig.

13:13.001 --> 13:14.569
Shh! My husband. Shh!

13:14.669 --> 13:16.046
Damn you!

13:16.296 --> 13:18.656
Wait! We were talking about acrobatics.

13:18.756 --> 13:19.908
Oh, acrobatics.

13:20.008 --> 13:21.826
I was showing him how to do a backbend.

13:21.926 --> 13:23.411
You never take your eyes off her.

13:23.511 --> 13:27.081
You're always standing
under her trapeze, looking up her legs.

13:27.181 --> 13:28.124
I see you.

13:28.224 --> 13:30.084
Because we're planning this routine.

13:30.184 --> 13:33.563
Sure you are.
What do you take me for anyway?

13:34.063 --> 13:36.216
And I wanted to have a baby with you.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.718
I know. We'll continue this later.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.929
- Later?
- I know, but I don't wanna have a baby.

13:41.029 --> 13:42.972
- Oh, you're such a pig.
- I told you...

13:43.072 --> 13:44.574
You are a pig.

13:44.699 --> 13:45.808
But, I told you a thousand times.

13:45.908 --> 13:47.435
I don't want a baby with you anyway.

13:47.535 --> 13:50.396
I don't want a baby
if you were the last man on earth,

13:50.496 --> 13:52.148
I don't want a baby with you.

13:52.248 --> 13:53.274
Good!

13:53.374 --> 13:55.818
You're never gonna have to see me again.

13:55.918 --> 13:57.886
Good. Good riddance.

13:58.838 --> 14:00.511
I like my freedom.

14:06.512 --> 14:07.497
Oh, Doctor.

14:07.597 --> 14:08.665
What do you want, Kleinman?

14:08.765 --> 14:10.208
I'm sorry to disturb you.

14:10.308 --> 14:11.709
Can I come in, just for a minute?

14:11.809 --> 14:14.562
Would it be possible? I have a question.

14:15.897 --> 14:17.548
Are you in on the plan?

14:17.648 --> 14:18.883
Of course I am.

14:18.983 --> 14:20.510
Didn't you think I would be?

14:20.610 --> 14:23.363
I wanna find out my assignment.

14:23.571 --> 14:26.099
Please, don't disturb anything.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.642
No, no, no, I wouldn't think of it.

14:27.742 --> 14:31.542
I just wanna find out
my participation in the plan, you know.

14:32.121 --> 14:34.565
Of course, I wouldn't mind
having a little drink though.

14:34.665 --> 14:35.692
A drink?

14:35.792 --> 14:38.111
You know, the fog. It's a little damp.

14:38.211 --> 14:40.603
So I, you know...

14:40.703 --> 14:42.907
But not if it's an imposition.

14:43.707 --> 14:47.888
You know, I've never been here before.
This is an interesting...

14:49.639 --> 14:50.623
Oh.

14:50.723 --> 14:52.225
It's cheerful.

14:52.767 --> 14:56.317
I'm performing an unusual
amount of autopsies these days.

14:56.521 --> 14:59.821
Yes, I'm sure.
That's probably what accounts for

14:59.941 --> 15:02.677
so many of those
human fingers lying around.

15:02.777 --> 15:04.470
You don't generally see that.

15:04.570 --> 15:08.700
I guess the, the maid doesn't
get in that often to straighten up, so...

15:09.200 --> 15:14.172
My interest in all this murder business
is entirely scientific.

15:14.497 --> 15:16.249
I'm sure, I'm sure.

15:16.582 --> 15:19.210
I'm determined to use this opportunity

15:19.502 --> 15:22.346
to find out something definitive about

15:23.089 --> 15:24.887
the nature of evil.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.897
Why is the killer the way he is?

15:31.514 --> 15:35.690
Sometimes certain impulses
that can drive an insane man to murder

15:35.935 --> 15:38.734
inspire others to highly creative ends.

15:39.564 --> 15:43.301
Once I have him here, on this table,

15:43.401 --> 15:46.701
dismembered and scrutinized

15:47.822 --> 15:49.620
in minute detail,

15:50.700 --> 15:53.686
then I shall know
the answer with certainty to questions

15:53.786 --> 15:56.539
that now I can only speculate on.

15:57.248 --> 16:00.798
Yeah, but it's
not possible that under the microscope

16:01.002 --> 16:02.570
there's something
that you could never see?

16:02.670 --> 16:06.925
What are you implying?
Uh, a spiritual element?

16:07.717 --> 16:11.261
A soul that lives on after we're dead?

16:12.305 --> 16:13.477
A God?

16:18.519 --> 16:20.863
Ask him if there's anything else.

16:23.483 --> 16:25.531
What are you thinking now?

16:25.902 --> 16:28.262
I just must remember next time

16:28.362 --> 16:30.890
I go out to a restaurant...

16:30.990 --> 16:33.118
...not to order the sweetbreads.

16:34.577 --> 16:36.625
Kleinman, you'd better go.

16:36.954 --> 16:39.252
The time is growing very short.

16:39.832 --> 16:44.087
So, there's nothing you can tell me about
my participation in the plan?

16:47.924 --> 16:49.176
I'll go.

16:59.727 --> 17:01.946
The doctor was no help at all.

17:02.855 --> 17:06.942
This is ridiculous. Where is everybody?

17:07.944 --> 17:10.446
Unless, this is part of the plan.

17:11.821 --> 17:14.349
Maybe they have me under surveillance.

17:14.450 --> 17:18.454
If anything bad happens,
they'll come running out and grab me.

17:19.372 --> 17:21.773
Unless they don't come running out.

17:21.874 --> 17:25.720
But they could never think that
I'd be any match for a maniac.

17:27.128 --> 17:30.975
A deranged person is supposed to
have the strength of ten men.

17:32.176 --> 17:36.602
I have the strength of
one small boy with polio.

17:38.474 --> 17:40.626
Quiet, quiet, quiet!

17:40.726 --> 17:43.855
It's Bretschneider. He's been strangled.

17:44.814 --> 17:47.158
The killer may still be near.

18:12.842 --> 18:14.594
Poor Bretschneider.

18:15.678 --> 18:17.351
He had no enemies.

18:37.742 --> 18:39.768
Don't be afraid.

18:40.369 --> 18:42.313
I'm sorry I scared you.

18:42.413 --> 18:45.713
Oh, you... You really did scare me.

18:46.876 --> 18:49.925
I didn't see you
standing there in the shadows.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.472
It's such a foggy night.

18:53.716 --> 18:55.844
I was just going into town.

18:58.179 --> 19:00.581
You should be indoors.

19:01.081 --> 19:02.871
It's not safe.

19:02.971 --> 19:04.839
I don't care.

19:06.562 --> 19:08.064
What was that?

19:08.981 --> 19:10.449
I don't know.

19:14.362 --> 19:16.681
What are you doing out here tonight?

19:16.781 --> 19:20.081
I'm used to the streets.
It's how I make my living.

19:21.994 --> 19:22.995
Oh.

19:23.913 --> 19:25.415
What do you do?

19:26.290 --> 19:29.009
Oh, I... I work with the circus.

19:30.002 --> 19:32.425
Well, you should have stayed there.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.240
Don't you know what's lurking
in this fog?

19:34.340 --> 19:36.138
I'm never going back.

19:38.052 --> 19:39.395
Oh, I see.

19:41.514 --> 19:42.957
That's how it is.

19:43.057 --> 19:45.334
Except I have no place to sleep.

19:45.884 --> 19:48.103
And I'm getting cold.

19:50.064 --> 19:51.966
Come on, I'll find you
a place at the house.

19:52.066 --> 19:53.342
The house?

19:53.442 --> 19:54.989
The whorehouse.

19:55.403 --> 19:56.450
Me?

19:56.737 --> 19:58.681
It's warm. You'll get something to eat.

19:58.781 --> 20:01.142
It's a lot safer in there
than it is out here.

20:01.242 --> 20:03.019
Come on. Stop looking at me like that.

20:03.119 --> 20:05.121
You'll have your privacy.

20:06.997 --> 20:09.796
Hi, everybody. This is Irmy.

20:09.959 --> 20:12.445
She's with the circus.
