36:58.550 --> 37:01.202
a hotel open at this hour, you know.

37:01.302 --> 37:03.872
I think I should wake up my fiancée
and you could sleep on the sofa.

37:03.972 --> 37:05.040
Oh, no, I don't want to wake anybody up.

37:05.140 --> 37:07.208
She would be glad to.

37:07.308 --> 37:09.652
You know, it's... It's so foggy.

37:10.019 --> 37:12.363
He strikes in the fog, you know.

37:14.065 --> 37:15.884
You didn't hear anything, did you?

37:15.984 --> 37:17.552
- Footsteps.
- You're so tense.

37:17.652 --> 37:21.122
Well, I'm usually in bed, you know,
this time of night.

37:21.948 --> 37:23.224
What would you do

37:23.324 --> 37:25.352
if you came face to face
with the killer?

37:25.452 --> 37:27.729
I'd throw pepper in his eyes.

37:27.829 --> 37:28.813
Really?

37:28.913 --> 37:30.815
My landlady put some pepper
in my pocket.

37:30.915 --> 37:32.734
I think I could handle myself.

37:32.834 --> 37:34.381
Kleinman!

37:35.044 --> 37:36.279
What are you doing here?

37:36.379 --> 37:38.740
Oh, my God! You scared me.

37:38.840 --> 37:40.367
Who is she?

37:40.467 --> 37:41.743
She's just a friend.

37:41.843 --> 37:43.912
Do you happen to know my assignment?

37:44.012 --> 37:45.622
Who gave you permission to socialize?

37:45.722 --> 37:47.165
I'm not socializing.

37:47.265 --> 37:50.460
You know, she's... Maybe you recognize her.
She's with the circus.

37:50.560 --> 37:52.608
She's the sword-swallower.

37:52.771 --> 37:55.632
She's unescorted.
I was just walking next to her.

37:55.732 --> 37:57.801
We're getting closer to the zero hour.

37:57.901 --> 37:59.594
Yeah? So what do I do?

37:59.694 --> 38:01.596
- Don't you know?
- No. That's the point.

38:01.696 --> 38:03.181
You know, you got me up,
in the middle of the night

38:03.281 --> 38:05.016
and no one's told me
what I'm supposed to be doing.

38:05.116 --> 38:09.104
Kleinman, I swear, if anyone is killed or
hurt as a result of your incompetence.

38:09.204 --> 38:11.272
No, I don't know enough
to be incompetent.

38:11.372 --> 38:12.691
You know, they don't tell me
what I'm supposed to...

38:12.791 --> 38:14.734
All right, just don't make a noise,
and listen to me.

38:14.834 --> 38:17.428
There is someone lurking up the alley.

38:18.713 --> 38:19.885
Well...

38:20.173 --> 38:24.349
Shall I just start weeping
or would you like me to break into a run?

38:24.719 --> 38:26.329
It's a chance to trap him.
Whoever it is.

38:26.429 --> 38:27.872
No. I don't wanna trap anybody.

38:27.972 --> 38:30.125
We'll get reinforcements.
There's three of us only.

38:30.225 --> 38:32.794
What they say about you
isn't true, is it?

38:32.894 --> 38:37.715
You're not really a coward
or a worm or a yellow-belly?

38:38.090 --> 38:41.445
No, but keep going.
You're in the right column.

38:42.403 --> 38:43.972
All right, I'll circle around the block.

38:44.072 --> 38:45.181
You head straight up the alley.

38:45.281 --> 38:47.726
No, I don't wanna do this.
No, this is, this is trouble.

38:47.826 --> 38:50.311
- I can go with you.
- No! She's gonna go with me.

38:50.411 --> 38:51.938
What good are you? You're a small woman.

38:52.038 --> 38:53.415
- She's gonna, you know...
- I'm okay.

38:54.582 --> 38:59.154
You go first. It'll throw his timing off
if he sees a body.

38:59.254 --> 39:00.405
Go on, Kleinman.

39:00.505 --> 39:03.634
It'll take me a moment or two
to get round the other side.

39:08.304 --> 39:10.557
Keep ahead of me.

39:16.271 --> 39:18.399
Those are my knees knocking.

39:21.401 --> 39:24.200
Stay calm.
The trick is not to show fear.

39:35.623 --> 39:37.296
There he is! Look!

39:38.251 --> 39:41.129
Grab him! Grab him!

39:46.843 --> 39:48.536
- Kleinman!
- Mr. Paulsen!

39:48.636 --> 39:49.662
You know him?

39:49.762 --> 39:51.289
This is my boss.
He's the head of my firm.

39:51.389 --> 39:54.209
- What are you doing here?
- I'm part of the plan, Your Grace.

39:54.309 --> 39:56.336
- Why did you attack me?
- I thought...

39:56.436 --> 39:58.379
"Thought"?
Since when do you think, Kleinman?

39:58.479 --> 40:00.465
Yes, you're right,
Your Majesty. I shouldn't have...

40:00.565 --> 40:02.592
I had a suspicion you were incompetent,

40:02.692 --> 40:04.636
hiding behind
the efforts of your co-workers.

40:04.736 --> 40:06.387
Don't let him talk to you like that.

40:06.487 --> 40:07.972
- What?
- He was peeping in that window

40:08.072 --> 40:09.390
watching that woman getting undressed.

40:09.490 --> 40:10.517
- How dare you.
- He was.

40:10.617 --> 40:11.851
No, no, no. Don't listen to her.

40:11.951 --> 40:13.853
She's swallowed too many sharp objects.

40:13.953 --> 40:15.522
Don't be a doormat for this Peeping Tom.

40:15.622 --> 40:17.065
This is my boss. He's my boss.

40:17.165 --> 40:18.566
To think that I was undecided

40:18.666 --> 40:20.568
about your abilities versus Simon Carr.

40:20.668 --> 40:23.238
Yes, what can I say, sir?
You looked dangerous.

40:23.338 --> 40:24.781
I didn't know you were merely peeping.

40:24.881 --> 40:26.908
Why didn't you attend
to your function in the plan?

40:27.008 --> 40:28.243
I don't know my function.

40:28.343 --> 40:30.787
You don't know?
You unreliable simpleton.

40:30.887 --> 40:32.455
- Don't call him a simpleton.
- No, well put.

40:32.555 --> 40:34.582
- It was well put.
- You're a disgusting old man.

40:34.682 --> 40:36.000
No, don't say that. Go away.

40:36.100 --> 40:37.961
Go away, Miss. Whoever you are, go away.

40:38.061 --> 40:39.921
Go away, go away. Leave us alone.

40:40.021 --> 40:41.273
Paulsen?

40:42.065 --> 40:45.134
You gave us quite a scare. I sent Kleinman
round here to check you out.

40:45.234 --> 40:47.303
He was just, you know, looking in the
window. There was a woman...

40:47.403 --> 40:49.722
Mark my words, he'll be a detriment.

40:49.822 --> 40:51.641
No, sir. Don't say that, sir.
Let me block your hat.

40:51.741 --> 40:52.767
No, give me that.

40:52.867 --> 40:54.102
Sir, you... I'm sorry.

40:54.202 --> 40:55.854
He's always been a liability
with my firm.

40:55.954 --> 40:57.897
I'm only just now beginning
to realize it.

40:57.997 --> 41:00.591
Mr. Paulsen, I didn't mean it. You...

41:01.209 --> 41:02.301
Sir!

41:04.253 --> 41:05.721
Irmy!

41:13.721 --> 41:14.813
Irmy!

41:30.446 --> 41:31.472
We're closing.

41:31.572 --> 41:33.370
Just one beer? Please?

41:44.419 --> 41:49.095
Did anyone see a blonde woman
wandering around alone?

41:49.340 --> 41:50.717
Short hair.

41:51.426 --> 41:55.538
Oh, mercy.
We never know when we have a good thing.

41:55.638 --> 41:57.686
We always have to ruin it.

41:58.224 --> 42:00.602
I know exactly how you feel.

42:01.144 --> 42:03.693
The earthly paradise known as woman.

42:04.272 --> 42:06.525
All we'll ever know of heaven.

42:08.735 --> 42:10.737
All we need know of hell.

42:12.655 --> 42:15.808
I made love to a woman tonight
that was sheer perfection.

42:15.908 --> 42:17.018
And it's true it was in a brothel,

42:17.118 --> 42:20.998
but somehow this one
didn't have that used, jaded quality.

42:21.122 --> 42:23.250
I never do it with whores.

42:23.958 --> 42:25.735
You start out with a burning desire

42:25.835 --> 42:29.885
and end up the next day with a burning
sensation, if you know what I mean.

42:30.798 --> 42:33.472
Yes, but this one was so irresistible.

42:34.302 --> 42:36.020
Sweet and innocent.

42:36.929 --> 42:40.479
But under the sheets, a tigress.

42:41.267 --> 42:46.148
A violent, screaming,
passionate jungle cat.

42:47.356 --> 42:49.050
You mean a good actress.

42:49.150 --> 42:50.652
She swore not.

42:51.736 --> 42:54.831
Well, you're very young, my friend.
Very naive.

42:55.990 --> 42:57.725
She dug her nails into my back.

42:57.825 --> 42:58.810
I'm sure.

42:58.910 --> 43:01.396
And then she yelled
"Don't stop! Don't stop!"

43:01.496 --> 43:05.149
Yes. And stuck her tongue inside my
mouth and wiggled it around.

43:05.249 --> 43:07.923
I'm sure it was well worth the $20.

43:08.669 --> 43:11.343
Twenty? I paid her 700.

43:11.589 --> 43:14.263
Yeah. Yeah, sure. Tell me another one.

43:14.425 --> 43:18.020
I'm afraid you've
never made love with a sword-swallower.

43:20.515 --> 43:22.188
I beg your pardon?

43:24.519 --> 43:26.587
She claims she never took money before.

43:26.687 --> 43:29.736
And if she was acting,
she should win a prize.

43:29.941 --> 43:34.071
It's true that I put on
a heroic performance, if I do say so myself.

43:34.362 --> 43:36.347
She brought out the stallion in me.

43:36.447 --> 43:40.042
And when she said she loved it,
I believe she was sincere.

43:40.368 --> 43:44.522
I think she's got a lover who doesn't
service her too well, you know?

43:44.622 --> 43:46.215
Some poor clown.

43:46.874 --> 43:49.718
But I showed her
what a good one felt like.

43:53.131 --> 43:55.884
What's wrong? You look incredulous.

43:56.926 --> 44:00.180
I swear, the dirtier I got,
the more she screamed.

44:00.680 --> 44:03.583
I gave her the best time
she's had in years,

44:03.683 --> 44:05.626
and I believe she loved it.

44:05.726 --> 44:09.026
Not that I have
any further urge for her, you know.

44:09.147 --> 44:12.151
The difference between
love and lust, I guess.

44:15.570 --> 44:19.245
When my friend wakes up,
tell him I went back to Felice's.

44:20.616 --> 44:23.061
This is crazy.
Can't I talk you out of it?

44:23.161 --> 44:26.522
No, I don't want it.
I want the church to have it, all of it.

44:26.622 --> 44:28.858
Yeah, but you're talking about $700.

44:28.958 --> 44:30.318
- That's a lot.
- Six hundred and fifty.

44:30.418 --> 44:31.986
I had to pay a fine.

44:32.086 --> 44:34.572
But so, you know, you...
But it's your money.

44:34.672 --> 44:35.656
Why give it away?

44:35.756 --> 44:37.992
Because I'm ashamed of the way I got it.

44:38.092 --> 44:39.619
Listen, I'm sure you didn't steal it.

44:39.719 --> 44:42.097
No. I slept with somebody for it.

44:43.556 --> 44:44.540
Yes?

44:44.640 --> 44:47.484
Just one person.
Does that make me a whore?

44:47.894 --> 44:50.379
Well, only by the dictionary definition.

44:50.479 --> 44:52.340
Anyway, I'm giving it to the church.

44:52.440 --> 44:53.966
Yeah, but that seems so silly.

44:54.066 --> 44:57.616
You know... It's work, you know.

44:57.945 --> 44:59.514
I'm sure you didn't do it for fun.

44:59.614 --> 45:00.765
No.

45:00.865 --> 45:03.976
But you know something?
It turned out to be fun.

45:04.076 --> 45:07.188
Here. Would you take it in there for me
and give it to them?

45:07.288 --> 45:09.440
- Me?
- Yeah. For the poor.

45:09.540 --> 45:12.527
I just can't bring myself
to go in there tonight.

45:12.627 --> 45:14.721
Please? Come on.

45:21.677 --> 45:23.162
- Excuse me, I'm...
- Yes?

45:23.262 --> 45:25.248
I just need a minute of your time.

45:25.348 --> 45:27.708
I think you can see that we're busy.

45:27.808 --> 45:29.836
I just... Just for one...

45:29.936 --> 45:32.280
Put Kramer's name on the list.

45:32.772 --> 45:35.716
Have you seen his sketches
and his photo studies?

45:35.816 --> 45:37.885
Just for a minute,
if I might have your attention...

45:37.985 --> 45:39.178
Just for one moment.

45:39.278 --> 45:41.701
Didn't you hear him say we're busy?

45:43.282 --> 45:44.475
Are you Kleinman?

45:44.575 --> 45:46.998
Yes. Yes, I am. Yes.

45:48.496 --> 45:49.964
Don't forget.

45:53.000 --> 45:54.902
Why is he putting my name on the list?

45:55.002 --> 45:56.070
You've been warned twice now.

45:56.170 --> 45:58.948
What is this list? Might I just ask?

45:59.048 --> 46:00.449
I have a donation to make.

46:00.549 --> 46:01.826
The poor box is in the front.

46:01.926 --> 46:04.162
No, this doesn't fit in the poor box.

46:04.262 --> 46:06.581
Kleinman, you want me to take you in?

46:06.681 --> 46:08.900
No, no, no. I have $650.

46:09.350 --> 46:10.835
Six hundred and fifty dollars?

46:10.935 --> 46:12.253
Don't worry, it's not stolen.
He thinks it's stolen.

46:12.353 --> 46:13.462
Where did you get it?

46:13.562 --> 46:16.549
I assure you.
My friend said I should donate it.

46:16.649 --> 46:17.884
Where did your friend get it?

46:17.984 --> 46:19.969
I don't think that
we don't have to pry excessively.

46:20.069 --> 46:23.073
We humbly accept
this token from the faithful.

46:23.614 --> 46:26.893
And I think
that we know how to show gratitude

46:26.993 --> 46:29.792
when someone performs an act of charity.

46:37.003 --> 46:38.721
Manna for the poor.

46:40.464 --> 46:41.490
Did you do it?

46:41.590 --> 46:44.059
- Yeah, I took care of it.
- Oh.

46:45.043 --> 46:47.188
I feel so much better now.

46:47.288 --> 46:49.265
- Good.
- Are you a religious person?

46:49.557 --> 46:50.833
Me? No, I'm not.

46:50.933 --> 46:53.085
You're the second person tonight
to ask me that question.

46:53.185 --> 46:55.630
The doctor, may he rest in peace,
wanted to know.

46:55.730 --> 46:58.090
- Do you pray ever?
- No.

46:58.190 --> 47:00.051
'Cause my people pray
in a different language,

47:00.151 --> 47:01.969
you know, I never understood
what they were saying.

47:02.069 --> 47:05.579
For all I know, you know,
they were requesting their own troubles.

47:06.240 --> 47:07.241
Help me.

47:08.743 --> 47:12.213
Please help me. Help.

47:12.371 --> 47:14.315
- Are you all right?
- Who is that?

47:14.415 --> 47:15.837
I'm hungry.

47:17.001 --> 47:19.254
I need to buy food and milk.

47:21.756 --> 47:23.929
My husband is dead.

47:24.800 --> 47:26.035
I'm alone.

47:26.135 --> 47:29.355
We're friends.
You know, you're among friends.

47:30.514 --> 47:32.667
Go back and get some of the money back.

47:32.767 --> 47:33.834
What are you talking about?

47:33.934 --> 47:36.003
I want her to have half of it.

47:36.103 --> 47:38.339
I can't get the money back.
I just gave them the money.

47:38.439 --> 47:41.008
So what? Just ask for half back.

47:41.108 --> 47:44.136
You just gave it to them.
They give it to the poor, don't they?

47:44.236 --> 47:47.556
Well, theoretically they do,
but a lot of it is used

47:47.656 --> 47:50.751
to buy costumes
and velvet pillows and stuff.

47:51.243 --> 47:52.395
Please.

47:52.495 --> 47:53.496
Oh...

47:54.747 --> 47:57.108
My friend asked me
if I could possibly come

47:57.208 --> 47:59.485
and just have
half the money back that I gave you.

47:59.585 --> 48:01.462
Just $300. It would...

48:03.255 --> 48:04.598
Thank you.

48:06.300 --> 48:09.975
Kleinman.
Is that with an "ei" or an "ie"?

48:10.638 --> 48:12.561
Put a circle around it.

48:16.977 --> 48:19.571
Eve. Eve, open up.

48:19.980 --> 48:21.482
It's Kleinman.

48:22.149 --> 48:26.262
Eve. Eve, it's an emergency.
It's me. It's Max.

48:26.362 --> 48:27.638
This is a bad idea.

48:27.738 --> 48:30.662
No, she's a wonderful girl.
Very intelligent.

48:30.783 --> 48:31.830
Eve!

48:32.326 --> 48:33.418
Eve!

48:34.328 --> 48:37.064
What are doing here at this hour?
Who is this?

48:37.164 --> 48:38.607
Can we come in?

48:38.707 --> 48:39.959
What's going on?

48:40.126 --> 48:42.903
She's a friend of mine.
She has no place to sleep tonight.

48:43.003 --> 48:45.301
I told her she could sleep on your sofa.

48:45.464 --> 48:46.741
You did?

48:46.841 --> 48:50.345
We're sorry.
It's much too much of an imposition.

48:50.761 --> 48:53.372
You dare to wake me out of a deep sleep

48:53.472 --> 48:56.726
so that some
complete stranger can sleep on my sofa?

48:57.184 --> 48:59.837
She's not a complete stranger.
She's a friend.

48:59.937 --> 49:02.840
You know, Eve,
I personally vouch for her.

49:02.940 --> 49:04.863
I apologize, Miss.

49:05.776 --> 49:07.219
Kleinman, have you been drinking?

49:07.319 --> 49:10.289
Have I been... When do I ever drink?

49:10.531 --> 49:12.767
Since when is she your friend?

49:12.867 --> 49:15.936
Since tonight.
I met her at the police headquarters.

49:16.036 --> 49:18.773
They brought her in
when they raided the brothel.

49:18.873 --> 49:20.316
It's not what it sounds like.

49:20.416 --> 49:23.465
You know, everybody
makes one mistake now and then.

49:24.253 --> 49:26.572
Kleinman, what are you
doing out at this hour?

49:26.672 --> 49:30.159
I'm part of a vigilante committee
to help catch the maniac.

49:30.259 --> 49:31.761
By doing what?

49:32.636 --> 49:34.434
I don't exactly know.

49:35.806 --> 49:38.980
Go home, Kleinman.
And take your friend with you.

49:40.478 --> 49:44.073
You've got some nerve.
We'll discuss this in the morning.

49:49.736 --> 49:52.240
Boy, Eve is a cold fish.

49:52.740 --> 49:54.583
There. I said it.

49:54.950 --> 49:58.750
Is it hard for you to admit
certain things to yourself?

49:59.580 --> 50:03.426
Usually it is, yes.
But for some reason tonight is different.

50:04.293 --> 50:07.763
You know, it's a strange feeling
to be up at this hour.

50:08.172 --> 50:11.267
The city is so odd
when everybody's asleep.

50:11.592 --> 50:12.618
You know, it's like a

50:12.718 --> 50:13.744
- different place completely.
- Mmm-hmm.

50:13.844 --> 50:17.289
There's no civilization.
The stores are closed.

50:17.389 --> 50:19.250
You know, it's so free.

50:19.350 --> 50:21.899
It's an odd feeling for me.

50:22.811 --> 50:26.566
I feel I could run down
the street naked and nobody would...

50:27.566 --> 50:30.445
You know, it has a really free feeling.

50:31.237 --> 50:32.388
I've never seen it from up here.

50:32.488 --> 50:34.723
I've never really taken
the time to look.

50:34.823 --> 50:38.394
It's so pretty, you know, some of
the stars are beginning to come up.

50:38.494 --> 50:41.043
The fog is just breaking a tiny bit.

50:42.081 --> 50:45.335
You see that very bright
star up in that direction?

50:45.751 --> 50:46.752
Mmm-hmm.

50:47.002 --> 50:48.988
For all we know, that star could have

50:49.088 --> 50:51.115
disappeared a million years ago,

50:51.215 --> 50:55.812
and it's taken the light from it
a million years to reach us.

50:56.514 --> 50:59.558
Oh, so what are you saying?
That star is not there?

50:59.723 --> 51:01.625
That it might not be there.

51:01.725 --> 51:04.170
Even though I can see it
with my own eyes?

51:04.270 --> 51:05.738
That's right.

51:07.147 --> 51:10.384
That's a very, uh,
disquieting thought, you know.

51:10.484 --> 51:12.094
Because when
I see something with my own eyes,

51:12.194 --> 51:14.013
I like to know that it's actually there.

51:14.113 --> 51:16.557
'Cause otherwise, you know,
a person could sit down in a chair

51:16.657 --> 51:17.600
and break his neck.

51:17.700 --> 51:20.186
You know,
you have to be able to rely on things.

51:20.286 --> 51:21.896
That's very, very important.

51:21.996 --> 51:23.439
You know who has
these thoughts all the time?

51:23.539 --> 51:26.901
Schultz the tailor.
He thinks that nothing is real at all

51:27.001 --> 51:30.426
and that everything
exists only in the dream of a dog.

51:31.338 --> 51:33.466
But this is real, isn't it?

51:33.674 --> 51:36.769
And beautiful.
Just think about it for a minute.

51:37.344 --> 51:39.079
Here we are, we're two strangers,

51:39.179 --> 51:41.457
and we're out in the night,
and it's just

51:41.557 --> 51:43.525
so peaceful and quiet.

51:44.351 --> 51:46.921
And suddenly there's,
there's a little clearing in the fog

51:47.021 --> 51:49.865
and we can see right out there
to the stars.

51:50.482 --> 51:53.076
Doesn't this moment just seem perfect?

51:54.403 --> 51:59.099
Yes, but, you know,
it passes so quickly.

51:59.199 --> 52:01.894
Look. Even now the fog
is starting to go back in.

52:01.994 --> 52:03.062
And you know, everything...

